judgments.dispoDesc:
12 mo. DJA - Upon successful completion - State will dismiss.  Conditions: 
1) No new ciminal offenses; 
2) Notify DA's Office & Clerk of Courts of any change of address/phone number within 48 hours; 
3) Comply with all terms of diversion supervision, including reporting to Diversion Coordinator on the 3rd Wednesday of each month;
4) Pay diversion program supervision fees of $25/month to DA;s Office; 
5) Pay restitution if requested at or before the plea hearing to the DA's office on behalf of victim, MS.  None has been reqeusted at this time:  
6) Write letters of apology to victim,  MS, and to the officers.  Letters must be signed & include acknowledgment of the event & that what happened was inappropriate, summary of what has been learned throught this process, & include actual expression or remorse.  Letters to be provided to Diversion Coordinator with the first 30 days of supervision; 
7) Make reasonable attempts to locate and/or maintain full-time employment/education & provide documentation to Diversion Coordinator;
8) Have no contact with Adam Ganser & Jeremy Shoemaker (co-defendants in Case 15-CM-340);
9) Not to possess and/or consume alcohol and/or  controlled substances during period of DJA, without valid prescription;
10) Attend & successfully complete an alcohol & drug assessment within 90 days, & complete any recommeded follow-up counseling/treatment prior to end of diversion term.  Defendant to provide release of Program Records Waiver to Diversion Coordinator;
11) Submit to random UA's when requested by Diversion Coordinator and/or treatment provider;
12) Undergo Anger Management evaluation withion 90 days & complete any follow-up counseling/treatment prior to end of diversion term.  To maintain all scheduled appointments & comply with all recommendations, & provide a release of Program Records Waiver to Diversion Coordinator.

